THE SENATE
S.B. NO.
THIRTY-THIRD LEGISLATURE. 2026
STATE OF HAWAII
C.D. 1
A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO PERSONNEL.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAH:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that the job title
2 "secretary" has become outdated in both the public and private
3 sectors, leading many organizations to adopt more contemporary
4 titles such as "administrative assistant" or "executive
5 assistant". To ensure that the State's job titles remain
6 current and appealing to potential applicants, the department of
7 human resources development has renamed the civil service
8 secretary series to "administrative assistant" and the
9 administrative assistant series to "executive specialist",
10 effective July 16, 2024, This modernization aligns the State's
11 job titles with prevailing industry standards and enhances its
12 ability to attract and retain qualified employees.
13 Therefore, the purpose of this Act is to update state
14 position titles by changing "private secretary" to "executive
15 assistant" and "secretary" to "administrative assistant", where
16 applicable.
