10 amended to read as follows:
11 "§353-65 Paroles; rules. The Hawaii paroling authority
12 may establish rules, with the approval of the governor and the
13 director of corrections and rehabilitation not inconsistent with
14 this part, under which any prisoner may be paroled but shall
15 remain, while on parole, in the legal custody and under the
16 control of the paroling authority, and be subject, at any time
17 until the expiration of the term for which the prisoner was
18 sentenced, to be taken back within the enclosure of the prison.
19 The rules shall have the force and effect of law. Full power,
20 subject to this part, to enforce the rules, to grant, and to
21 revoke paroles is conferred upon the paroling authority. The
